 This dataset contains country aggregate results using the PaRIS International Dataset. Results are age- and sex-standardised, and account for distinct variance at country, primary care practice, and patient levels.

• Target population: people aged 45 and over who had at least one contact with a primary care practice in the six months preceding the sampling date.
• PaRIS uses two questionnaires: one for patients – PaRIS Patient Questionnaire (PaRIS-PQ) – and one for primary care practices – PaRIS Primary Care Practice Questionnaire (PaRIS-PCPQ).

• PaRIS Patient Questionnaire (PaRIS-PQ)
• PaRIS Primary Care Practice Questionnaire (PaRIS-PCPQ)

 PaRIS aims to improve healthcare by assessing and publishing patient-reported measures across OECD and participating countries to facilitate international comparison and cross-country learning.

 Read the report here: Does Healthcare Deliver?

For a detailed description of the PaRIS 10 key indicators presented in this dataset, see Table 2.1 of the report.

For a complete description of the methods and data behind the results, see Chapter 7: PaRIS Data and Methods of the report.

